# Component Development Standards

## React Components
- Use functional components with TypeScript
- Export as default exports: `export default function ComponentName()`
- Use proper TypeScript interfaces for props
- Follow the pattern: `function ComponentName() { ... } export default ComponentName;`

## Styling Guidelines
- Use Tailwind CSS for all styling
- Prefer neutral colors: `bg-white`, `text-gray-900`, `text-gray-600`
- Use `cursor-pointer` for interactive elements
- Keep designs simple and clean

## Component Structure
```typescript
"use client"; // Only if needed for client-side features

import { ComponentProps } from "@/components/ui/component";
import { Icon } from "lucide-react";

/**
 * Component description
 * 
 * @component
 */
function ComponentName() {
  return (
    <div className="component-styles">
      {/* Component content */}
    </div>
  );
}

export default ComponentName;
```

## shadcn/ui Integration
- Use existing shadcn/ui components from src/components/ui/
- Import with: `import { Component } from "@/components/ui/component"`
- Extend with additional props when needed
- Maintain accessibility standards

## Responsive Design
- Use responsive Tailwind classes: `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`
- Test on mobile, tablet, and desktop
- Use `grid` and `flex` for layouts
- Ensure touch-friendly interactive elements